  "texts": [
    "A qualitative example of such molecules is shown in Supplementary Fig. 4.",
    "For these reasons, PatCID has a clear advantage over SciFinder and Reaxys with respect to the coverage of sections within documents.",
    "Contrary to SureChEMBL, Google Patents and Reaxys, given a query molecule, PatCID not only finds the documents referencing this molecule but also keeps provenance to its explicit location within documents.",
    "For patent documents that can span hundreds of pages and contain thousands of similar molecules, this feature is very useful.",
    "It allows to interactively explore documents, easily referring to neighbouring content of the query molecule."
